claim: Outsider music is created by musicians who are part of the commercial music industry.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Outsider music is created by musicians who are not part of the commercial music industry and who write music that ignores standard musical or lyrical conventions , either because they have no formal training or because they disagree with conventional rules .
